'(3708) 1974 FV 1' is a Jupiter Trojan
approximately 80 kilometers in diameter. It completes one orbit around the Sun
in just under 12 years. It was discovered on March 21, 1974 at Cerro El Roble
observatory in Chile. It has the lowest designation number of the
unnamed minor planets.
